# 7. 思いがけない提案

Ichika: Let's see... Oh, this looks like the tea shop we saw online.
Kanade: They have so many different types... We should be able to find exactly what everyone needs.
Ichika: Yes, this is actually really exciting!
Ichika: Still... I couldn't believe it when it turned out that we'd come up with the same idea.
Kanade: Me neither. Wanting to help everyone relax after working so hard is one thing, but the odds of us both deciding to buy them tea seem astronomical.
Ichika: Why did you decide to get tea, Kanade?
Kanade: The tea Ms. Mochizuki always buys really helps calm my nerves whenever I drink it.
Kanade: So, I thought that tea could help do the same for everyone.
Ichika: Yes, I see...
Ichika: Then, let's do our best to find some tea that everyone is going to love!
???: Huh?
Minori: Kanade! Ichika!
Airi: Oh, hey! What a pleasant surprise!
Kanade: Huh...? Hanasato? Momoi?
Ichika: Wait a second... Are you two here to shop for that segment?
Airi: That's right. Are you two here because you decided on what gifts to get?
Kanade: Yes, we both gave it a lot of thought and...
Kanade: ...and so, we decided to buy everyone tea.
Minori: Really...?! Yeah, that does sound nice and relaxing!
Airi: Interesting...
Minori: Is something the matter, Airi?
Airi: You two made a great choice! But...
Airi: If you're gonna get them tea, then why not take it one step further by actually serving it to them?
Ichika: Serving them tea...?
Airi: Yeah! We'll call it Operation: White Day Tea Party!
Minori: O-Operation: White Day Tea Party...?!
Minori: Wait, what do you mean?
Airi: You want to give everyone a chance to relax, right, Yoisaki?
Airi: So, instead of just giving them the tea... Why not throw them a tea party where they can have both a fun and relaxing time?
Kanade: Oh...
Minori: I agree! It'd be so much fun to have a tea party together when it's nice out!
Ichika: Yeah, that does sound fun...
Ichika: And they'd probably really enjoy it... Especially Honami.
Kanade: I agree... Mizuki and the others as well.
Kanade: (Actually, what about Mafuyu...?)
Airi: What do you say? We'd be more than happy to help you two with this.
Minori: Yeah, I'll help as much as you need!
Kanade: Oh... B-But... I'm not sure how I'll do...
Ichika: ...
Ichika: Let's give it a try, Kanade.
Kanade: What...?
Ichika: I'm also a little worried...
Ichika: But I want to give it a try. Because I can't think of anything that would make me happier than seeing them all smile at this tea party.
Kanade: Oh...
Ichika: You want them to feel relaxed, and I want them to see them smile...
Ichika: And I think this tea party will allow us to accomplish both.
Kanade: Yes, you're right...
Kanade: I really like this idea.
Airi: Then, let's do it!
Airi: We have a lot to prepare... But let's start by picking a nice location!
Ichika: Where can we have a tea party with everyone...?
Airi: There are going to be a lot of people, we'd need so somewhere with enough space for all of us.
Ichika: Someone's home might be too small... So, I guess we'd need to rent a big room or hold it outside...?
Kanade: Outside...?
Kanade: Oh, then... How about that place?
Mafuyu: I'm back.
Kanade: Okay, napkins, garbage bags, plates... I think that's everything we need.
Mafuyu: What are you doing?
Kanade: Oh, Mafuyu, welcome back.
Kanade: I'm getting everything ready for White Day. We're throwing a tea party.
Kanade: Our plan is to give everyone a chance to relax since they're always working so hard.
Mafuyu: I see.
Kanade: *Nod* So, Mafuyu, would you like to join us...?
Mafuyu: Me?
Mafuyu: I...think I'm okay. I don't know if it counts as feeling relaxed, but I feel at ease here.
Kanade: Okay, I understand.
Kanade: But I actually got some tea just for you, Mafuyu. So, if you decide to change your mind, it'd be nice to see you there.
Mafuyu: ...
Kanade: Oh, but you don't have to force yourself to go. We can always have your tea here.
Mafuyu: Where are you having this tea party?
Kanade: Umm... Nonogi Park.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: I'll think about it.
Kanade: Okay, thank you.
